DD37-DD52 - DIP RAM 256K*4 (from 286 Motherboard :) )

 Power of all chips - maximum number pin, ground - maximum/2 number pin.
Warning:  memory vcc - pin 10; gnd - pin 20.  EVERY chip MUST have
blocking capacitor!

 Resistors: any 1-4k

 Diode: any.

 Jumpers:  switches JMx between ground and Vcc.

n2K - switch 1.5mb RAM between addresses $C00000 and $600000
JM1 =0   fast ram on
    =1   fast ram off
JM2 =0   2ьс fast ram
    =1   1ьс fast ram
JM3 =0   ram overlays rom
    =1   ram doesn't overlay rom
JM3 JM2
 0   0   ram from address 60(C0)-77(D7), "rom" from address 78
 0   1   ram from address 60(C0)-67(C7), "rom" from address 68(C8)
 1   0   ram from address 60(C0)-7F(D7) & (78)-(7F), rom from address F8 (kickstart)
 1   1   ram from address 60(C0)-6F(CF), rom from address F8 (kickstart)
JM4 =0   ROM ($F80000) write disabled
    =1   ROM ($F80000) write enabled
JM5 =0   HDD (and CC0) enabled
    =1   HDD disabled

 Some old HDDs require 1k pullup resistors.


